item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Henry Miller
item.description: "Develop an interest in life as you see it; the people, things, literature, music - the world is so rich, simply throbbing with rich treasures, beautiful souls and interesting people. Forget yourself." -- Henry Miller

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Henry Miller
item.description: "I have no money, no resources, no hopes. I am the happiest man alive." -- Henry Miller

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Henry Miller
item.description: "Do not be duped by little duties. Do not be a chore man all your days." -- Henry Miller

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "Live, travel, adventure, bless, and don't be sorry." -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "I like too many things and get all confused and hung-up running from one falling star to another till i drop. This is the night, what it does to you. I had nothing to offer anybody except my own confusion." -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "Happiness consists in realizing it is all a great strange dream" -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "You don't know what to say to me because the kingdom is within...flesh and blood's dream...so you fly now, pay later, all of us...I mean actually it's PAY NOW, FLY LATER" -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "Life must be rich and full of loving--it's no good otherwise, no good at all, for anyone." -- Jack Kerouac

item.title: Cmcquade17 add a quote by Jack Kerouac
item.description: "Let nature do the freezing and frightening and isolating in this world. let men work and love and fight it off." -- Jack Kerouac
